SCRAPIE, SHEEP - SWITZERLAND: OIE
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 25 May 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties (OIE), Emergency Alert Messages
[edited]
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/040524CHE.htm>

Scrapie in Switzerland
---------------------------
(Date of previous outbreak of scrapie in Switzerland reported to the OIE:
June 1999).
Information received on 24 May 2004 from Dr Hans Wyss, Director of the
Federal Veterinary Office, Bern:
Date of the report: 24 May 2004.
One case of scrapie was detected on 18 May 2004 in a farm with 12 sheep in
Zurich canton. According to immunohistochemistry and post-mortem
examination, this case is atypical (probably NOR98). Further diagnostic
testing is in progress.
Source of agent / origin of infection: unknown.
Control measures: movement restrictions.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Switzerland last reported Scrapie in June of 1999. Scrapie is a
transmissible encephalopathy of sheep which does not infect humans. See
the moderator commentary for further details on scrapie transmission among
species, the distribution in European countries, and problems with
reporting of this disease worldwide. - Mod.PC]
